accessibility.text: Using Composer in a Drupal project
Using Composer in a Drupal project
Composer can be used to add dependencies to a Drupal project. It can be used in the following ways.
Adding composer.json to a Drupal module, theme, profile or drush library.
To install packages from sources instead of simple zip archives, you will need git, svn, fossil or hg depending on how the package is version-controlled.
Composer is multi-platform, it run equally well on Windows, Linux and OSX.
